<h6 style="text-align:center;" data-zesty-id="content:text:1:41">Athletic&nbsp;Programs</h6>
<p data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:2:17">
	Each year over 1,000 youth participate in The Salvation Army of Wake County&nbsp;Athletics Programs, learning the importance of team play and good sportsmanship. Always maintaining a Christ-centered atmosphere, there are pre-game devotions and prayers for each sport. Here, children are taught that winning means having fun, learning fundamental skills, and being a part of a team where they make&nbsp;a difference.&nbsp;For more information contact our Youth Programs at <a href="tel:919-832-6918" target="">919-832-6918</a>.
</p>
<div class="my-2" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-sm:3:6"></div>
<p style="text-align:center;" data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:4:39">
